hopobject.body: Do you know what extension he's on? apollo pharmacy dindigul address The triple bill opened with the UK premiere of Justin Peck’s Murder Ballads, a smooth, fresh-faced piece by a young New York City Ballet dancer who is beginning to make waves as a choreographer. To a score by The National’s guitarist Bryce Dessner, with starkly evocative lighting by Brandon Stirling Baker, which fills the stage with rich colour, he sets the cast gambolling and skipping as if at a hoe-down.
